            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'return on investment (ROI) for marketing campaigns?', 'answer': 'ROI for marketing campaigns is calculated as the revenue generated from the campaign minus the cost of the campaign, divided by the cost of the campaign. Example formula: = (Revenue - Cost) / Cost.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'adjusted rate of return?', 'answer': 'Adjusted rate of return is calculated as the actual return adjusted for risk factors and inflation. Example formula: = Actual_Return - Risk_Adjustment - Inflation_Adjustment.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'debt service coverage ratio (DSCR)?', 'answer': 'DSCR is calculated as net operating income divided by total debt service. Example formula: = Net_Operating_Income / Total_Debt_Service.'},
