            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'interest coverage ratio?', 'answer': 'Interest coverage ratio is calculated as earnings before interest and taxes divided by interest expense. Example formula: = EBIT / Interest_Expense.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'return on sales?', 'answer': 'Return on sales is calculated as operating profit divided by sales revenue. Example formula: = Operating_Profit / Sales_Revenue.'},
