            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'financial leverage ratio?', 'answer': 'Financial leverage ratio is calculated as total assets divided by total equity. Example formula: = Total_Assets / Total_Equity.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'liquidity ratio?', 'answer': 'Liquidity ratio is calculated as liquid assets divided by current liabilities. Example formula: = Liquid_Assets / Current_Liabilities.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'return on equity (ROE) for a startup?', 'answer': 'ROE for a startup is calculated as net income divided by shareholders equity. Example formula: = Net_Income / Shareholders_Equity.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'annualized return on investment?', 'answer': 'Annualized return on investment is calculated as the geometric average annual return over a specified period. Example formula: = (Ending_Value / Beginning_Value) ^ (1 / Number_of_Years) - 1.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'payout ratio?', 'answer': 'Payout ratio is calculated as dividends paid divided by net income. Example formula: = Dividends_Paid / Net_Income.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'price-to-book (P/B) ratio?','answer':  'P/B ratio is calculated as the market price per share divided by the book value per share. Example formula: = Market_Price_Per_Share / Book_Value_Per_Share.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'earnings yield?', 'answer': 'Earnings yield is calculated as earnings per share divided by the market price per share. Example formula: = Earnings_Per_Share / Market_Price_Per_Share.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'average daily balance?', 'answer':  'Average daily balance is calculated as the sum of daily balances divided by the number of days in the period. Example formula: = Sum_of_Daily_Balances / Number_of_Days.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'average inventory?',  'answer': 'Average inventory is calculated as the sum of beginning and ending inventory divided by two. Example formula: = (Beginning_Inventory + Ending_Inventory) / 2.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'total revenue from sales?', 'answer':  'Total revenue from sales is calculated as the selling price per unit multiplied by the number of units sold. Example formula: = Selling_Price_Per_Unit * Number_of_Units_Sold.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'total cost of goods sold (COGS)?',  'answer': 'COGS is calculated as beginning inventory plus purchases minus ending inventory. Example formula: = Beginning_Inventory + Purchases - Ending_Inventory.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'depreciation expense using the straight-line method?', 'answer':  'Depreciation expense using the straight-line method is calculated as the cost of the asset minus its residual value, divided by the useful life of the asset. Example formula: = (Cost_of_Asset - Residual_Value) / Useful_Life.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'amortization expense?', 'answer':  'Amortization expense is calculated as the cost of an intangible asset divided by its useful life. Example formula: = Cost_of_Intangible_Asset / Useful_Life.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'financial ratio?', 'answer':  'Financial ratio is calculated as one financial metric divided by another. Example formula: = Metric_A / Metric_B.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'break-even point in units for a new product?',  'answer': 'Break-even point in units is calculated as fixed costs divided by the contribution margin per unit. Example formula: = Fixed_Costs / Contribution_Margin_Per_Unit.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'break-even point in sales dollars?', 'answer':  'Break-even point in sales dollars is calculated as fixed costs divided by the contribution margin ratio. Example formula: = Fixed_Costs / Contribution_Margin_Ratio.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'average return on equity (ROE)?',  'answer': 'Average ROE is calculated as the average of the return on equity over a specific period. Example formula: = Average_ROE.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'average return on assets (ROA)?',  'answer': 'Average ROA is calculated as the average of the return on assets over a specific period. Example formula: = Average_ROA.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'internal rate of return (IRR) for a project?',  'answer': 'IRR is calculated as the discount rate that makes the net present value of all cash flows from a project equal to zero. Example formula: = IRR(Cash_Flows).'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'present value of annuity?', 'answer':  'Present value of annuity is calculated as the sum of the present values of all future payments in the annuity. Example formula: = Payment * [(1 - (1 + Rate)^-Number_of_Periods) / Rate].'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'present value of a single sum?', 'answer': 'Present value of a single sum is calculated as the future value divided by (1 plus the discount rate) raised to the number of periods. Example formula: = Future_Value / (1 + Discount_Rate)^Number_of_Periods.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'future value of a single sum?',  'answer': 'Future value of a single sum is calculated as the present value multiplied by (1 plus the interest rate) raised to the number of periods. Example formula: = Present_Value * (1 + Interest_Rate)^Number_of_Periods.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'future value of annuity?', 'answer':  'Future value of annuity is calculated as the sum of future values of all payments in the annuity. Example formula: = Payment * [(1 + Rate)^Number_of_Periods - 1] / Rate.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'capital gains yield?', 'answer':  'Capital gains yield is calculated as the change in stock price divided by the initial stock price. Example formula: = (Ending_Price - Beginning_Price) / Beginning_Price.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'dividend yield?',  'answer': 'Dividend yield is calculated as the annual dividend divided by the market price per share. Example formula: = Annual_Dividend / Market_Price_Per_Share.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'total return on investment?',  'answer': 'Total return on investment is calculated as the sum of capital gains and dividend income divided by the initial investment. Example formula: = (Capital_Gains + Dividend_Income) / Initial_Investment.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'rate of return on an investment?', 'answer':  'Rate of return is calculated as the gain or loss from an investment divided by the initial investment. Example formula: = (Ending_Value - Beginning_Value) / Beginning_Value.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'adjusted gross income (AGI)?', 'answer':  'AGI is calculated as gross income minus adjustments such as retirement contributions and student loan interest. Example formula: = Gross_Income - Adjustments.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'taxable income?', 'answer':  'Taxable income is calculated as AGI minus deductions and exemptions. Example formula: = AGI - Deductions - Exemptions.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'effective tax rate?', 'answer':  'Effective tax rate is calculated as total tax liability divided by taxable income. Example formula: = Total_Tax_Liability / Taxable_Income.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'marginal tax rate?', 'answer':  'Marginal tax rate is calculated as the rate applied to the last dollar of income. Example formula: = Marginal_Tax_Rate.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'alternative minimum tax (AMT)?', 'answer':  'AMT is calculated as the tax liability under the AMT system, which is an alternative to the regular tax calculation. Example formula: = AMT_Liability.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'total tax liability?', 'answer':' Total tax liability is calculated as the sum of regular tax and any additional taxes such as AMT. Example formula: = Regular_Tax + Additional_Taxes.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'effective annual yield (EAY)?',  'answer': 'EAY is calculated as (1 + nominal interest rate / compounding periods) ^ compounding periods - 1. Example formula: = (1 + Nominal_Rate / Compounding_Periods) ^ Compounding_Periods - 1.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'annual percentage yield (APY)?', 'answer':  'APY is calculated as the effective annual rate of interest earned on an investment. Example formula: = (1 + Nominal_Rate / Compounding_Periods) ^ Compounding_Periods - 1.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'return on investment for a project?', 'answer':  'ROI for a project is calculated as the net profit from the project divided by the initial investment. Example formula: = Net_Profit / Initial_Investment.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'annualized return?', 'answer':  'Annualized return is calculated as the average annual return over a specific period, adjusted for the length of the investment. Example formula: = (Ending_Value / Beginning_Value) ^ (1 / Number_of_Years) - 1.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'cash flow from operations?', 'answer':  'Cash flow from operations is calculated as net income plus adjustments for non-cash items and changes in working capital. Example formula: = Net_Income + Non_Cash_Expenses + Changes_in_Working_Capital.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'free cash flow?',  'answer': 'Free cash flow is calculated as cash flow from operations minus capital expenditures. Example formula: = Cash_Flow_From_Operations - Capital_Expenditures.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'operating profit margin?',  'answer': 'Operating profit margin is calculated as operating profit divided by net sales. Example formula: = Operating_Profit / Net_Sales.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'average collection period?',  'answer': 'Average collection period is calculated as accounts receivable divided by average daily sales. Example formula: = Accounts_Receivable / Average_Daily_Sales.'},
