            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'working capital?', 'answer':  'Working capital is calculated as current assets minus current liabilities. Example formula: = Current_Assets - Current_Liabilities.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'quick ratio?',  'answer': 'Quick ratio is calculated as (current assets minus inventories) divided by current liabilities. Example formula: = (Current_Assets - Inventories) / Current_Liabilities.'},
            {'category': 'Economics', 'question': 'cash ratio?', 'answer':  'Cash ratio is calculated as cash and cash equivalents divided by current liabilities. Example formula: = Cash_and_Cash_Equivalents / Current_Liabilities.'},
